flowRoot.flowPara: This file provides a predictable SVG input for idforge-qatest(1) command to validate production processes implemented by idforge-render(1) and idforge-locale(1) commands.
This file helps to implement the following validations:
• Create PNG files for different sizes, colors and locales, based on SVG and PO files.
• Create PNG files with dynamic information based on translation markers expansion.
• Create PNG files combining several PNG images on other PNG images.
• Convert PNG files to other image formats (e.g., JPG, TIF).

As result of processing the =CONFIG_SECTIONS= configuration sections, using the production standards implemented by idforge-render(1) command, you must see a composition made of the following elements:
• Full opacity idFORGE logotype on document header.
• Semi-transparent idFORGE symbol on document background.
• Full opacity idFORGE symbols in different colors and sizes on document footer.
